  "description": "## MacOS_Default_ActivateSso\n\n**Type:** Device Configuration  \n**Platform:** macOS\n\n### Description\nEnables the macOS Azure AD Single Sign-On extension to provide seamless sign-on on targeted macOS devices. The policy configures browser_sso_interaction_enabled = 1 to allow the SSO extension to interact with browsers and disable_explicit_app_prompt = 1 to suppress explicit prompts when apps request SSO tokens; shared device mode is disabled (per-user SSO). No bundle ID access control list is defined, so there are no explicit app allow/deny entries configured. All other device feature settings (content caching, power controls, login window text, etc.) remain at their defaults/not configured.",
